            "notes": "The deck revolves around creating a prison-like environment for the opponent by using various enchantments to control the board. Sythis, Harvest's Hand is used as the commander to draw cards whenever enchantments enter the battlefield, ensuring a steady stream of resources. The deck includes a mix of removal spells like Swords to Plowshares and Journey to Nowhere, as well as enchantments like Ghostly Prison and Sphere of Safety to make it difficult for the opponent to attack or cast spells. It also includes cards like Greater Auramancy and Sterling Grove to protect its own enchantments. Overall, the strategy is to establish a lock on the game and grind out a victory through card advantage and attrition."
